Q_DESC:
Ristha is 3 years old. She is very intelligent. She found a sentence The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog in her story book. She noticed that this sentence contains all the alphabets in English. 

She told this to her mom. Mom told her that this sentence is a Pangram (Pangrams are sentences constructed by using every letter of the alphabet at least once.)

She got really interested in this. She started checking every sentences she go through. She got tired after a while..
Given a sentence s, help Ristha to check if it is a pangram or not.

Input Format

Input consists of a string s.

Constraints 
Length of s can be at most 10^3(1=|s|=10^3)  and it may contain spaces, lower case and upper case letters. Lower-case and upper-case instances of a letter are considered the same.

Output Format

Output a line containing pangram if s is a pangram, otherwise output not pangram.
TESTCASE_1:
We promptly judged antique ivory buckles for the next prize
###---###SEPERATOR---###---
pangram
TESTCASE_2:
We promptly judged antique ivory buckles for the prize
###---###SEPERATOR---###---
not pangram
TESTCASE_3:
The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog
###---###SEPERATOR---###---
pangram
TESTCASE_4:
The quick brown fox jumps  lazy dog
###---###SEPERATOR---###---
not pangram
